\begin{document}$$ f = {\sqrt {\frac{{\eta ^{2} }} {{1 - \eta ^{2} }}} }. $$\end{document} An effect size (f) of > 0.4 was considered to reflect a strong effect (Cohen 1988). The analyses were performed using SPSS (SPSS, Inc., Chicago, IL, USA).

